# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldMage8
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "More than a month had passed since Sarah had returned from Bagrad."
    new "More than a month had passed since Sarah had returned from Bagrad."

    old "Most of her days had been spend since studying under the guidance of Razaphel."
    new "Most of her days had been spend since studying under the guidance of Razaphel."

    old "One book, then the next."
    new "One book, then the next."

    old "Some of it had been frustrating, never truly knowing what any of it amounted to, but in another part she was grateful."
    new "Some of it had been frustrating, never truly knowing what any of it amounted to, but in another part she was grateful."

    old "Grateful for the distraction. Grateful to have something she could put her mind to."
    new "Grateful for the distraction. Grateful to have something she could put her mind to."

    old "Samayra had been one of the rare few friends in an otherwise lonely house."
    new "Samayra had been one of the rare few friends in an otherwise lonely house."

    old "She was happy that the girl was here."
    new "She was happy that the girl was here."

    old "All alone, Sarah had only Razaphel for company."
    new "All alone, Sarah had only Razaphel for company."

    old "They spoke, but Sarah could never shake the feeling that something seperated the two of them."
    new "They spoke, but Sarah could never shake the feeling that something seperated the two of them."

    old "Early this particular morning, Sarah had made her way through the house and found herself back at Xan's private study."
    new "Early this particular morning, Sarah had made her way through the house and found herself back at Xan's private study."

    old "She couldn't remember if she walked her on her own, or perhaps whether the house had guided her here."
    new "She couldn't remember if she walked her on her own, or perhaps whether the house had guided her here."

    old "Sarah wasn't even sure if the difference mattered."
    new "Sarah wasn't even sure if the difference mattered."

    old "As she slowly made her way around his study, looking over at all the different collections of books and artifacts, she could see his desk from the corner of her eyes."
    new "As she slowly made her way around his study, looking over at all the different collections of books and artifacts, she could see his desk from the corner of her eyes."

    old "And on the desk, the book of their order. The Hollow World."
    new "And on the desk, the book of their order. The Hollow World."

    old "Sarah slowly made her way towards the desk."
    new "Sarah slowly made her way towards the desk."

    old "Reaching down with the tip of her fingers, she lifted up the cover and flipped the book open."
    new "Reaching down with the tip of her fingers, she lifted up the cover and flipped the book open."

    old "Massive. indecipherable."
    new "Massive. indecipherable."

    old "She wasn't sure if even after all of Razaphel's guidance, whether she had gotten any closer to making sense of it."
    new "She wasn't sure if even after all of Razaphel's guidance, whether she had gotten any closer to making sense of it."

    old "The book had become like a splinter in her mind, impossible to ignore."
    new "The book had become like a splinter in her mind, impossible to ignore."

    old "Near her, Sarah could see the air stir as the spirit manifested itself."
    new "Near her, Sarah could see the air stir as the spirit manifested itself."

    old "You're back here again."
    new "You're back here again."

    old "Sarah kept studying the book."
    new "Sarah kept studying the book."

    old "Round and round I go."
    new "Round and round I go."

    old "But I never really seem to get anywhere with this."
    new "But I never really seem to get anywhere with this."

    old "Sarah tapped the book with her knuckles."
    new "Sarah tapped the book with her knuckles."

    old "I wanted you to be prepared."
    new "I wanted you to be prepared."

    old "Prepared."
    new "Prepared."

    old "For when you came to know of the knowledge within it."
    new "For when you came to know of the knowledge within it."

    old "Hoping that you would be ready when the time came."
    new "Hoping that you would be ready when the time came."

    old "Razaphel...I have done as you asked of me. As much as could be expected of anyone."
    new "Razaphel...I have done as you asked of me. As much as could be expected of anyone."

    old "And still you give me riddles."
    new "And still you give me riddles."

    old "I can't live like this. Always in the dark."
    new "I can't live like this. Always in the dark."

    old "Perhaps I have been too harsh on you."
    new "Perhaps I have been too harsh on you."

    old "Denied you answers that have long been owed to you."
    new "Denied you answers that have long been owed to you."

    old "Sarah turned to face the spirit."
    new "Sarah turned to face the spirit."

    old "Then give them to me. Tell me the answers to the questions I don't even know how to ask."
    new "Then give them to me. Tell me the answers to the questions I don't even know how to ask."

    old "The spirit drifted through the room."
    new "The spirit drifted through the room."

    old "It liked to speak, but now it seemed hesitant."
    new "It liked to speak, but now it seemed hesitant."

    old "I am afraid."
    new "I am afraid."

    old "Sarah found herself smiling, surprised at the sudden confession."
    new "Sarah found herself smiling, surprised at the sudden confession."

    old "Afraid? I thought nothing scared you."
    new "Afraid? I thought nothing scared you."

    old "You would be a fool to think so, Sarah. There are things that strike fear even in the likes of me."
    new "You would be a fool to think so, Sarah. There are things that strike fear even in the likes of me."

    old "What are you afraid of?"
    new "What are you afraid of?"

    old "The spirit paused. Lingered."
    new "The spirit paused. Lingered."

    old "You have nothing to fear from me, Razaphel. I hold no animus against you."
    new "You have nothing to fear from me, Razaphel. I hold no animus against you."

    old "The spirit turned its face-mask towards her."
    new "The spirit turned its face-mask towards her."

    old "I have moved in the shadows of your world for too long."
    new "I have moved in the shadows of your world for too long."

    old "Long ago I imagined I could traverse this long arc, and often had I seen the path in is many fractious forms..."
    new "Long ago I imagined I could traverse this long arc, and often had I seen the path in is many fractious forms..."

    old "Now, so close to the moment, I find my resolve to be as weak and soft as the day I started."
    new "Now, so close to the moment, I find my resolve to be as weak and soft as the day I started."

    old "Sarah looked on the spirit, it's shape breaking apart, as if under some great stress."
    new "Sarah looked on the spirit, it's shape breaking apart, as if under some great stress."

    old "You're not making any sense, Razaphel. We are friends, I promise I won't hurt you, ever."
    new "You're not making any sense, Razaphel. We are friends, I promise I won't hurt you, ever."

    old "Forgive me."
    new "Forgive me."

    old "You are right."
    new "You are right."

    old "I have given you too many burdens, too many labors. The time for truth has come."
    new "I have given you too many burdens, too many labors. The time for truth has come."

    old "Whichever direction the stone may fall, I shall know that I have prepared the earth as much as I could have."
    new "Whichever direction the stone may fall, I shall know that I have prepared the earth as much as I could have."

    old "Sarah studied the spirit. Answers, finally."
    new "Sarah studied the spirit. Answers, finally."

    old "Out in the desert, far in the east beyond the great city of Bagrad, lies a city by the name of Nauyziri."
    new "Out in the desert, far in the east beyond the great city of Bagrad, lies a city by the name of Nauyziri."

    old "Travel there, and we shall do away with this secrecy."
    new "Travel there, and we shall do away with this secrecy."

    old "We will stand before one another as equals, and I shall hold back no more."
    new "We will stand before one another as equals, and I shall hold back no more."

    old "Nauyziri? I have never heard of that place."
    new "Nauyziri? I have never heard of that place."

    old "It has long been forgotten, one of the first cities to fall to the advance of the desert, many centuries ago."
    new "It has long been forgotten, one of the first cities to fall to the advance of the desert, many centuries ago."

    old "None still live there, but a Mythran host now occupies it."
    new "None still live there, but a Mythran host now occupies it."

    old "A Mythran army? Why?"
    new "A Mythran army? Why?"

    old "They are looking for something, buried in the sands of the city. Something they have been searching for, for a long time now."
    new "They are looking for something, buried in the sands of the city. Something they have been searching for, for a long time now."

    old "Sarah lowered her head, thinking."
    new "Sarah lowered her head, thinking."

    old "How can I get there?"
    new "How can I get there?"

    old "There is a door in this house, and it will bring you there, same as it once brought you to Bagrad."
    new "There is a door in this house, and it will bring you there, same as it once brought you to Bagrad."

    old "Sarah knew that the house connected to many spaces across the world, so the spirit's words seemed obvious in hindsight."
    new "Sarah knew that the house connected to many spaces across the world, so the spirit's words seemed obvious in hindsight."

    old "What am I supposed to find when I go there?"
    new "What am I supposed to find when I go there?"

    old "Go to Nauyziri. Buried beneath the sands you will find a black monolith."
    new "Go to Nauyziri. Buried beneath the sands you will find a black monolith."

    old "Go there and we shall speak, free of riddles and obscurities."
    new "Go there and we shall speak, free of riddles and obscurities."

    old "Sarah observed the spirit for a moment."
    new "Sarah observed the spirit for a moment."

    old "It had resumed its regular form, no longer distressed. Back to its unreadable state."
    new "It had resumed its regular form, no longer distressed. Back to its unreadable state."

    old "Then she nodded."
    new "Then she nodded."

    old "Alright, I will go to this city, as you asked, but I won't be lead around again."
    new "Alright, I will go to this city, as you asked, but I won't be lead around again."

    old "She stared at Razaphel intently."
    new "She stared at Razaphel intently."

    old "No more games."
    new "No more games."

    old "Only the truth."
    new "Only the truth."

    old "With that, the spirit faded."
    new "With that, the spirit faded."

    old "Alone again in the study, Sarah contemplated everything Razaphel had told her."
    new "Alone again in the study, Sarah contemplated everything Razaphel had told her."

    old "A strange city she had never heard of, on the edge of the world. An object, buried deep in the sand."
    new "A strange city she had never heard of, on the edge of the world. An object, buried deep in the sand."

    old "It all meant very little to her."
    new "It all meant very little to her."

    old "Except for the answers he finally promised her."
    new "Except for the answers he finally promised her."

    old "Sarah had spend the rest of the day preparing."
    new "Sarah had spend the rest of the day preparing."

    old "Gathering up supplies, some food and water, basic spell books, some spell reagants."
    new "Gathering up supplies, some food and water, basic spell books, some spell reagants."

    old "It wasn't much, but Sarah couldn't be sure what would be waiting for her on the other side. Best be prepared."
    new "It wasn't much, but Sarah couldn't be sure what would be waiting for her on the other side. Best be prepared."

    old "Standing near the edge of the room, watching her, was Samayra."
    new "Standing near the edge of the room, watching her, was Samayra."

    old "The girl seemed nervous."
    new "The girl seemed nervous."

    old "Why can't I come with you?"
    new "Why can't I come with you?"

    old "It's dangerous. It's dangerous in ways I don't even really understand."
    new "It's dangerous. It's dangerous in ways I don't even really understand."

    old "You'll be safe here, and I promise I'll be back as soon as I can be."
    new "You'll be safe here, and I promise I'll be back as soon as I can be."

    old "And even if something were to happen to me, at least I'd know that you would still be safe here."
    new "And even if something were to happen to me, at least I'd know that you would still be safe here."

    old "Samayra smiled at Sarah's concern for her."
    new "Samayra smiled at Sarah's concern for her."

    old "I'm tougher than you think."
    new "I'm tougher than you think."

    old "I know, and one day, I promise I'll show you ever corner of this world."
    new "I know, and one day, I promise I'll show you ever corner of this world."

    old "But if something were to happen to you there...I don't think I'd be able to forgive myself."
    new "But if something were to happen to you there...I don't think I'd be able to forgive myself."

    old "I understand, but you better get back here! Otherwise my only friend is Razaphel..."
    new "I understand, but you better get back here! Otherwise my only friend is Razaphel..."

    old "There are worse friends to have."
    new "There are worse friends to have."

    old "Sarah and Samayra exchanged the last of their goodbyes."
    new "Sarah and Samayra exchanged the last of their goodbyes."

    old "Sarah turned back towards the door that supposedly lead to the city. Nauyziri."
    new "Sarah turned back towards the door that supposedly lead to the city. Nauyziri."

    old "Standing before it, Sarah could feel a moment of hestitation come over her."
    new "Standing before it, Sarah could feel a moment of hestitation come over her."

    old "Here she was, same as before, cast out to the other side of the world on reasons she could hardly understand."
    new "Here she was, same as before, cast out to the other side of the world on reasons she could hardly understand."

    old "Some part of her also knew that this time, it was her decision."
    new "Some part of her also knew that this time, it was her decision."

    old "She went here, because she wanted to."
    new "She went here, because she wanted to."

    old "She was moving, though only in part, to her own choices."
    new "She was moving, though only in part, to her own choices."

    old "Freedom, even if it was a brutalized version of it."
    new "Freedom, even if it was a brutalized version of it."

    old "She smiled, comforted by the thought that whatever would happen, it would be her own choice."
    new "She smiled, comforted by the thought that whatever would happen, it would be her own choice."

    old "Sarah reached out with her hand, placing it on the handle of the door."
    new "Sarah reached out with her hand, placing it on the handle of the door."

    old "Then she pushed it open."
    new "Then she pushed it open."

    old "A rush of warm desert air came over her, flowing into the house."
    new "A rush of warm desert air came over her, flowing into the house."

    old "Sarah drew in a deep breath."
    new "Sarah drew in a deep breath."

    old "Then she took one step and crossed a million."
    new "Then she took one step and crossed a million."

    old "The door fell shut behind her, and in the air, she felt the sand of the desert."
    new "The door fell shut behind her, and in the air, she felt the sand of the desert."

    old "She had found the door that supposedly lead to the city. Nauyziri."
    new "She had found the door that supposedly lead to the city. Nauyziri."

